      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUR PINUP GIRL (4) finished 5.5 metres from the winner in third at Geelong over 2100m last start at her first career run. That debut effort is good enough to put her right in the finish. LOOKING FROM ABOVE (6) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when 7 metres from the winner in third over 1690m at Kilmore. Meets a comparable field and he can take this out. A ROCKN NIGHTMARE (7) is a three-year-old filly from the Freddy Taiba stable on debut. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw. Trial winner who looks above average and any push in betting will add to the confidence. SASSYS BOY (1) is a four-year-old entire by American Ideal from Born Again Sassy on debut. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Has strong trial form coming into this and is likely to attract plenty of interest from punters.",
